From: Dragos-Bogdan Chirila <dchirila@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] xwayland: guard damage_report against a NULL xwl_window

damage_report() already tolerates a NULL xwl_window in its first three
blocks (each is guarded with `if (xwl_window && ...)`), but its final block
dereferences xwl_window unconditionally:

    window_pixmap = screen->GetWindowPixmap(xwl_window->surface_window);
    if (xwl_is_client_pixmap(window_pixmap))
        xwl_screen->screen->DestroyPixmap(xwl_window_swap_pixmap(xwl_window, FALSE));

A damage report can fire for a window that has no associated xwl_window
(xwl_window_from_window() returns NULL for such a window). This happens in
the rootless-composite path when a client reconfigures/moves a window during
startup: ConfigureWindow -> xwl_move_window -> miMoveWindow -> damageCopyWindow
-> damageRegionAppend -> damage_report, with xwl_window == NULL, crashing the
whole guest X server with a NULL dereference at &((struct xwl_window *)0)->
surface_window (offset 0x40 on this ABI).

Mirror the guards already present earlier in the SAME function: with no
xwl_window there is no Wayland surface pixmap to swap, so skip the final block
instead of dereferencing NULL.

Reproduced deterministically on a seatless weston-headless + rootless-Xwayland
stack (Xwayland 24.1.x) by launching a normal GL application (Blender, OpenSCAD)
whose startup reconfigures its window; the same guarded build survives it.
Xwayland 23.2.x does not reach this crash, but the guard is correct there too.

--- a/hw/xwayland/xwayland-window.c
+++ b/hw/xwayland/xwayland-window.c
@@ -317,9 +317,11 @@ damage_report(DamagePtr pDamage, RegionPtr pRegion, void *data)
     if (xwl_window && xorg_list_is_empty(&xwl_window->link_damage))
         xorg_list_add(&xwl_window->link_damage, &xwl_screen->damage_window_list);

-    window_pixmap = screen->GetWindowPixmap(xwl_window->surface_window);
-    if (xwl_is_client_pixmap(window_pixmap))
-        xwl_screen->screen->DestroyPixmap(xwl_window_swap_pixmap(xwl_window, FALSE));
+    if (xwl_window) {
+        window_pixmap = screen->GetWindowPixmap(xwl_window->surface_window);
+        if (xwl_is_client_pixmap(window_pixmap))
+            xwl_screen->screen->DestroyPixmap(xwl_window_swap_pixmap(xwl_window, FALSE));
+    }
 }

 static void
